cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.NE, cs.CV 

The paper discusses the use of recurrent neural networks, specifically LSTMs, for learning from multivariate time series data in the context of clinical diagnosis. This falls under the broad category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves natural language processing (cs.CL) in the form of processing clinical notes. Additionally, the use of LSTMs falls under the category of neural networks (cs.NE) and the application of the models to medical imaging data is related to computer vision (cs.CV).
